      "faqs_v2_BYWkfd": {
        "type": "faqs-v2",
        "blocks": {
          "faq_A7twnN": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "What are the ingredients in Rejuvia?",
              "answer": "<p>Rejuvia contains a blend of 13 natural sleep ingredients including Melatonin (2mg), Valerian Root, Passionflower, Chamomile, Lemon Balm, 5-HTP, Magnolia Bark, Skullcap Root, and Ginkgo Biloba. Every ingredient is natural, purposeful, and triple lab-tested for purity and potency before it ships.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_kPjUwi": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "How quickly does Rejuvia work, and how long will I sleep?",
              "answer": "<p>Most customers feel Rejuvia working within 10-15 minutes of spraying. Because it absorbs directly under your tongue and into your bloodstream, it works significantly faster than pills or gummies that have to survive your digestive system first. Most customers report sleeping through the full night and waking up without grogginess.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_bnfb6i": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "Will I feel groggy the next morning?",
              "answer": "<p>No. Rejuvia is formulated with a low 2mg dose of melatonin paired with natural calming herbs, designed to support your body's own sleep cycle rather than sedate it. You wake up feeling rested and clear-headed, not foggy. If you've ever felt groggy from a sleeping pill, Rejuvia works very differently.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_iaepJi": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "What if Rejuvia doesn't work for me?",
              "answer": "<p>Your first order comes with a 90-day money-back guarantee. If you give it a real try and don't sleep better, contact us and we'll take care of you, no questions asked. We're confident enough in the formula to stand behind it completely.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_Yd6Xga": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "Is Rejuvia safe to use long-term?",
              "answer": "<p>Yes. Rejuvia is made with 100% natural, non-habit-forming ingredients. There's no tolerance buildup, no dependency, and no withdrawal. Thousands of customers have used it nightly for a year or more without ever needing to increase their dose. It works with your body, not against it.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_YArTEw": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "Do I need to take Rejuvia every night?",
              "answer": "<p>No, but most customers choose to. Rejuvia works on the nights you use it, so some people use it every night as part of their routine while others keep it on the nightstand for nights when sleep is harder to come by. Either way works. There's no dependency, so you can use it as often or as little as you need.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_eCabn9": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "Can I take Rejuvia if I have a medical condition?",
              "answer": "<p>We always recommend consulting your healthcare professional before starting any new supplement, especially if you have an existing medical condition. Unfortunately we are not able to provide medical advice. Your doctor will be best positioned to let you know if Rejuvia is right for you.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_hz8L79": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "How many sprays should I take?",
              "answer": "<p>Start with 6-8 sprays under your tongue or inside your cheek and let it sit for a few seconds before swallowing. If you find that's not enough, you can increase to 10-12 sprays. The beauty of a spray is that you control your dose precisely, unlike a pill or gummy where you're locked into whatever dose they decided for you.</p>"
            }
          },
          "faq_yjADWm": {
            "type": "faq",
            "settings": {
              "question": "What does Rejuvia taste like?",
              "answer": "<p>Fresh mint. It's light and pleasant, not medicinal or overwhelming. Most customers use it right after brushing their teeth as part of their bedtime routine, and the mint flavor fits naturally into that.</p>"
            }
          }
        },
